"""
You can define the document content in Markdown
by defining `f:markdown` in the TTL.

Images and embeds are more powerful than standard Markdown.
If you've defined an image as a Content (or a sub-type, like Picture), then you can embed it by its ID like this

`![](http://whatever.site/id)`

![](http://www.colourcountry.net/id/site/lingshed)

This allows you to take advantage of all the linked data goodness of FALSE, like descriptions and metadata for the image.
You can investigate these by clicking on the image.

You can embed any Content item, for example other documents written in Markdown.

![](http://www.colourcountry.net/id/site/reusable)

If you just want to embed an image from the internet, you can still do that, but you don't get <s>a cookie</s> the extra features.

